<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Aloft1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Aloft,</orth> adv., 1) above, opposed to below: <cit><quote>her chamber is a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. III, 1, 114</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that you be by her a., while we be busy below,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.244" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 244</bibl>.<lb />2) on high: <bibl n="shak. luc 505" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 505</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 78.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 78, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.254" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 254</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.471" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 471</bibl>. In <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 95</bibl> O. Edd. <emph>aloft,</emph> M. Edd. <emph>aloof.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>